President Barack Obama has announced the formation of a Presidential Delegation to the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia to offer condolences on the passing of Crown Prince Nayif bin Abd al-Aziz Al Saud. The delegation will be led by Secretary of Defense Leon E. Panetta and includes various other government officials such as the United States Ambassador to Saudi Arabia, the Director of the Federal Bureau of Investigation, and former officials from the Central Intelligence Agency and the White House. The delegation will visit Saudi Arabia on June 20, 2012, to offer their condolences to King Abdullah bin Abd al-Aziz Al Saud.